I've set up a brand new workspace and imported the same code. Also the same eclipse version. I have installed only the subclise plugin (for subversion), but I didn't let it manage the main project where I run the applications (I've checked out the files to different projects and created symlinks to the sources only). It now works very well, or at least I didn't get any disconnection from the VM. 

A thing I can give you as test case is that in the previous workspace I did setup lot of breakpoints (around 30) on codes like that

if ( <mycondition> ) {
  @SuppressWarnings("unused") int a=5;
}

the breakpoint being at @SuppressWarnings("unused") int a=5;

I cannot recall any other big difference between the old workspace and the new one. But if you have any further question don't hesitate to ask!

Thanks for your (very useful) help in developing such a nice IDE!
Vito Impagliazzo
